race.comment: DON'T SAY DO (13) boxed on bravely into second at Warren last start and will be further focused with blinkers applied. From a good draw and with a light weight, he's got every chance. LUCKY OZZIE (4) closed off nicely into third at Quirindi when resuming and is sure to have improved with that outing. Drawn well and shapes as a genuine contender.  ATLANTIC DIVA (12) resumes after two trials and should get every favour from the inside alley. Worth keeping safe. SHAKESPEARE'S GIRL (20) caught the eye fresh before failing last time at Hawkesbury. The draw makes things tricky, but she's capable of making her presence felt late.
